 <H1>Reasoning About FDs  (Contd.)</H1> 
 <P><UL>
<LI><H2>Couple of additional rules (that follow from AA):
</H2>
<UL>
<LI>Union:   If X       Y  and  X        Z,   then  X          YZ
<LI>Decomposition:   If X         YZ,   then  X        Y  and  X        Z
</UL></UL><UL>
<LI><H2>Example:    Contracts(cid,sid,jid,did,pid,qty,value), and:
</H2>
<UL>
<LI>C is the key:   C         CSJDPQV
<LI>Project purchases each part using single contract:  JP        C
<LI>Dept purchases at most one part from a supplier:  SD        P
</UL></UL><UL>
<LI><H2>JP      C,  C       CSJDPQV   imply   JP       CSJDPQV
</H2>
</UL><UL>
<LI><H2>SD      P   implies   SDJ      JP
</H2>
</UL><UL>
<LI><H2>SDJ      JP,   JP      CSJDPQV   imply   SDJ       CSJDPQV</H2>
</UL></P>
